This paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it deals with decoding of Low-Density Parity-Check codes, which is a well-known problem in information theory. It could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm for computing the projection onto the parity polytope. Additionally, it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories as these fields often deal with optimization problems and linear programming. Finally, it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as Low-Density Parity-Check codes are commonly used in communication systems.
